features.text:
**Introduction**

Under the background of automobile theme, aiming at the deficiencies of the existing automobile retail model, this topic proposes a pan-entertainment automobile consumption space and business model innovation of automobile enterprise brand alliance, and constructs three experience themed consumption spaces in the space design—theme They are future technology, family leisure and outdoor sports. Starting from the characteristics of automotive products, some digital and gamified retail experience models have been explored.

**Introduction**

In terms of service mode, the combination of online and offline, scene-based design mode is adopted to integrate the retail of automobile products with the daily entertainment life of users, and the design is optimized for the existing charging and parking space. This topic is an exploration of the auto exhibition space and service design by using the new Internet retail model under the trend of automobile industry innovation. more possibilities.

**Introduction**

Located in the centre of Manhattan under the Legislative Building, City Hall Station was one of the oldest subway stations that witnessed the history of New York City. Came in operation by 1904, it was well furnished in the Ro- manesque Revival style. City Hall Station was once the most attractive spot in New York; however, the rise in traffic made the City Hall Station no longer capable of accommodating the lengthened railcar, and it was eventually shut down by 1945. Despite that the station’s delicate interior was awarded as an interior heritage, it only opens on a limited schedule for minimum groups of people. City Hall Station remained unknown to the majority of citizens. The design to repurpose the station is an architecture based on a moving car- riage, appropriating the abandoned rail route as the site.

Designed based on the habit of human vision and combined with the site’s movement, it allows the City Hall Stationto become ac- cessible while remaining well protected. Moreover, the shift in out- er scenes also provides the visitors heterotopic experiences
